(## 6\) Rationale for ranking) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. **Outcome-first prioritization:** BP control is weighted highest because it is the primary) Tj
T*
(clinical outcome.) Tj
T*
(2. **Risk burden included:** High uncontrolled BP penalizes score strongly.) Tj
T*
(3. **Retention included:** Missed visits captures continuity-of-care failure.) Tj
T*
(4. **Scale-sensitive interpretation:** A volume threshold is used to avoid over-interpreting very) Tj
T*
(small facilities.) Tj
T*
(5. **Programmatic impact:** Large low-performing facilities \(e.g., Kadugannawa\) are high-priority) Tj
T*
(because district-level gains depend on them.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 7\) Prioritized intervention matrix for worst performers) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(| Priority | Facility | Main gap pattern | Immediate actions | Process KPI | Outcome KPI |) Tj
T*
(|---|---|---|---|---|---|) Tj
T*
(| 1 \(Critical\) | Pamunuwa | 100% missed, no outcome capture | Rapid data-quality and service-availability audit; generate full no-visit line list; active recall \(phone + field\); restore BP capture at every return visit | % overdue patients contacted; % return visits with BP measured | BP controlled % recovery from 0%; missed visits % reduction |) Tj
T*
(| 2 | Udathalawinna | Very high missed visits \(63%\) | Defaulter micro-plans by risk group; dedicated catch-up clinic slots; refill fast-track for overdue patients; weekly follow-up review | % missed patients reached; % returned within cycle | Missed visits % decline; BP controlled % increase |) Tj
T*
(| 3 | Mahakanda | High uncontrolled \(41%\) + high missed \(26%\) | Uncontrolled registry with protocolized titration; medicine stock assurance; adherence counseling bundle; early re-review for uncontrolled patients | % uncontrolled reviewed under protocol | Uncontrolled % decrease; controlled % increase |) Tj
T*
(| 4 | Narampanawa | High uncontrolled \(41%\) + high missed \(25%\) | Same model as Mahakanda; focus on appointment reliability and dose-intensification fidelity | % uncontrolled with treatment step-up documented | Controlled % increase; missed % decrease |) Tj
T*
(| 5 | Kadugannawa | Very high uncontrolled \(45%\) at high volume | High-volume uncontrolled stream; BP measurement quality check \(staff/device\); cohort review meetings; prioritize highest-risk cases first | % uncontrolled cohort reviewed monthly | Uncontrolled % drop from 45%; district-level controlled % gain |) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
